review_text: Dari sekian banyak WS yang ku kunjungi, entah kenapa di sini pelayanannya paling lama. Ga cuma sekali loh, SELALU LAMA. Padahal kondisi warung ga lagi rame. Ga tau ada kendala di kitchen atau emg aku selalu apes sm pelayanan di sini. Es tehnya dateng cepet tp steakny keluar 50 menit kemudian, dah gitu sampai aku selesai makan ada 1 menu yang belum dianter. Aku tanya ke staff ternyata GAK dibuatin. Yawes aku cancel aja. Makanan dan porsi WS ga banyak berubah dari dulu, enak, kecuali saosnya ga sih? Menurutku saos sambel yang dipake skrg kurang enak agak asem. Karena berkali2 kesel sama pelayanan yg lama banget di sini jadi aku bikin reviewnya. Semoga ada perbaikan dari management. WS lain ga selama ini soalnya padahal lebih rame.
review_translated_text: Of the many WS I visited, for some reason the service here took the longest. Not just once, ALWAYS A LONG TIME. Even though the shop is no longer busy. I dont know whether there are problems in the kitchen or whether Im always bad at the service here. The iced tea came quickly but the steak came out 50 minutes later, and that was until I finished eating, there was 1 menu that had not been delivered. I asked the staff and apparently it was NOT made. Yes, Ill just cancel. The food and portions WS havent changed much from before, its delicious, except for the sauce or not? In my opinion, the chili sauce used now is not delicious, its a bit sour. Because Ive been annoyed many times with the very slow service here, I made a review. Hopefully there will be improvements from management. The other WS wasnt this long because it was busier.

review_text: Food was good, worth the price. Cozy atmospheres, good service. Totally worth it. Theres some liquor though, so be careful what to order Food

Love the place and the ambiance! Food was delicious! The price was a bit extra for Solo but I think its worth it I tried to order their taco but then they said it was sold out... Weird thing was that an hour after that, I saw new customer in the next table able to order that. Kinda sad and confused about that. Service was quite fast but I think their waitress needed to smile and be more friendly... The only friendly staff that I encountered on my visit was the cashier I asked this male waitress to help me move the table to be closer to my chair, although he did help me with my request he seems so unfriendly, no smile, no nothing even tho I said thank you to him. So in my conclusion, their staff needs more training to be more friendly towards the customer I like this place. Nice food, nice place. My one problem was with their service. But other than that, I think its a good place and Im definitely gonna visit this place again.

Maaf sebelumnya, saya sampai ngga expect ke sini lagi... meskipun croissant nya enak menurut sy, tp kita makan ditempat butuh jg pelayanan yg bagus ya. Cerittanya pesan coffee tanpa gula (cappucino), eh yg datang manis banget... cek2 ternyata dibawah cup itu ada gula cairnya, dan saya bilang kalau saya tadi pesennya tanpa gula, Eh cup coffee kita langsung diambil... Kita nunggu agak lama, dan saya sempet lihat2 ke arah2 baristanya..mereka spt lg sibuk gmn nyelesein perkara, dan itu sy ngeliat ada yg nyicipin kopinya pakai sedotan. Akhirnya datanglah kopi kita, dan langsung dicoba lagi, wah... ternyata kita dpt zonk. Kopinya masih kerasa manis. Kita panggil lagi tuh waittressnya dan kita tanya, mba2 ini kok kopinya masih manis? Dan jawabnya langsung oh baik kita langsung ganti kopinya bu, nah yg kita minum ini apa mba? Kopi yg lama? Jawab lagi tuh  ga pa pa bu, kita ganti yg baru. Ane ngomong:  lhoh mba ga bisa gitu dong, sy bisa ngerasain ini kopinya manis ngga nya. Ini tadi kopinya yg lama terus? Nah akhirnya dijawab kalau tadi kopinya yg lama dan ditambah sama 1 shot coffee.. wah parah nih, gimana ya kok bisa gitu penyelesainnya... mngkin bisa ditraining lagi untuk hal2 yg seperti ini terjadi pegawainya harus berbuat seperti apa. Kelas amco resto nih kalau kacau gimana, sayang banget.. * akhirnya kopi kita figanti yg baru. Tapi tetep ya, ga seperti itu alur penyelesainnya.
review_translated_text: Sorry in advance, I didnt expect to come here again... even though the croissants are delicious in my opinion, but when we eat at a place we also need good service. The story is that I ordered coffee without sugar (cappuccino), but what came was really sweet... I checked and found that there was liquid sugar at the bottom of the cup, and I said that I had ordered without sugar. Hey, our coffee cup was immediately taken... We waited for a long time, and I looked around at the baristas... they seemed busy with how to solve a problem, and I saw someone sipping their coffee using a straw. Finally our coffee arrived, and immediately tried it again, wow... it turns out we got zonk. The coffee still tastes sweet. We called the waitress again and asked, ladies, how come the coffee is still sweet? And the answer was immediately oh okay, lets just change the coffee, maam, so what do we drink, sis? Old coffee? The answer was its okay, maam, well change to a new one. I said: You know, sis, I cant do that, I can feel whether this coffee is sweet or not. Is this old coffee? Well, finally the answer was that it was old coffee and added 1 shot of coffee. Wow, this is really serious, how can this be resolved... perhaps employees can be trained again for things like this to happen. What if the Amco Restaurant class goes awry, what a shame... * Finally we replaced our coffee with a new one. But still, thats not how the solution goes.

review_text: Harga mi 30ribuan, mienya tebal. Varian creamy kuahnya enak dan beneran creamy. Hakau udangnya juga enak dibandingkan beberapa tempat makan yang juga jual hakau. Sayangnya harga minumannya mahal dan gak berasa wah. Pesen es teh rasanya sama kyk teh 3ribuan bahkan kalah, mungkin sistemnya subsidi silang kali ya. Penyajiannya menurut saya agak kurang, mangkoknya terlalu kecil untuk porsi yang dihidangkan. Chilli oilnya kurang nampol rempahnya dan ada banyak menu yang kosong (ke sana pagi jam 9an). Kekurangan lainnya juga ada di pembayaran qris yang agak bermasalah sedikit. Parkir luas buat mobil dan motor. Suasananya nyaman dan cukup luas.
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih untuk masukannya kak, kami sudah beli mangkok dengan dimensi yang lebih besar, akan kami gunakan besok hari untuk memperbaiki penyajian dan supaya tidak tumpah ketika mie di aduk kak, xie-xie
review_translated_text: The price of noodles is 30 thousand, the noodles are thick. The creamy soup variant is delicious and really creamy. The shrimp hakau is also delicious compared to several places to eat that also sell hakau. Unfortunately the drink is expensive and doesnt taste good. Ordering iced tea tastes the same as if it costs 3 thousand or less, maybe its a cross-subsidy system, right? In my opinion, the presentation was a bit lacking, the bowl was too small for the portion served. The chilli oil doesnt have enough spices and there are lots of empty menus (went there in the morning at 9am). Another drawback is that QRIS payments are a bit problematic. Ample parking for cars and motorbikes. The atmosphere is comfortable and quite spacious.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your input sis, we have bought a bowl with larger dimensions, we will use it tomorrow to improve the presentation and so it doesnt spill when the noodles are stirred sis, xie-xie

review_text: Saya merupakan salah satu pelanggan setia restoran ini. Walaupun banyak teman saya yang bilang bahwa mi-nya seperti kurang matang atau apa, saya selalu membela bahwa itu merupakan konsep mereka. Bahkan suami saya sendiri pun tidak mau diajak makan di sini karena masalah pelayanannya yang buruk, tapi saya bertahan karena suka dengan cita rasanya. Akhirnya setiap ke sini saya selalu datang dengan mengajak teman saya. Saya juga selalu update di social media dan merekomendasikan restoran ini ke teman2 saya yang lain, bahkan teman saya yg dari luar kota. Tapi kemarin akan menjadi kali terakhir saya makan di sini. Kemarin selesai saya makan, salah satu tim mereka menghampiri ke meja menanyakan apakah saya sudah selesai makan. Kalau sudah, waktu saya sudah habis karena saya sudah 2 jam di sana dan mejanya mau dipakai customer lain. Saat itu hujan sangat deras, jadi saya sambil menunggu hujan agak reda. Kondisi di sana masih ada sekitar 6-8 meja yang kosong & tidak ada pelanggan yg datang. Tim wang li silahkan cek cctv 16/2/24 sekitar pukul 17.50-17.55. Lalu saya tanya, customer mana yang mau pakai tempat ini? Karena saya tidak melihat ada pelanggan yg datang atau mau pakai meja saya. Dijawab oleh tim mereka, ITU SUDAH MENJADI PERATURAN MEREKA. Baiklah, karena sudah diusir saya pergi.. Saya tanyakan ke kasir, kata kasir karena meja sofa isi 2 orang cuma ada 3 jadi siapa tau ada yang mau pakai di situ. HAH? Saya tanya, mana orang yg mau pakai? Kasir hanya meminta maaf atas kesalahan temannya. Jujur saya sangat kecewa dengan perlakuan tim mereka. Tidak masalah bila itu terjadi ketika kondisi resto memang sangat ramai & ada customer baru yang tidak mendapat meja. Saya akan dengan sukarela pergi. Tapi ini kondisi masih banyak meja yang kosong loh   Bahkan saya sudah sering makan di tempat yang lebih ramai, yg pelanggannya waiting list berpuluh2 orang berdiri, tapi nggak pernah tuh saya kena usir kaya di sini, apalagi sewaktu kejadian di resto ini masih banyak meja kosong. Bener-bener ga habis pikir. Secinta-cintanya saya sama makanan kalian, saya akan memilih makan di tempat lain daripada harus ke sini lagi. Semoga tim resto membaca review saya. Selamat, anda kehilangan salah satu loyal customer. Mulai hari ini SAYA. TIDAK. AKAN. DATANG. KE. SINI. LAGI. Terima kasih.
response_from_owner_text: Mohon maaf atas ketidaknyamanannya kak   ,  akan segera kami tindak lanjuti dan segera kami evaluasi. Menjadi bahan koreksi buat kami supaya kami bisa berbenah lebih baik lagi.
review_translated_text: I am one of the loyal customers of this restaurant. Even though many of my friends said that the noodles were undercooked or something, I always defended that that was their concept. Even my husband didnt want to be invited to eat here because of the bad service, but I stayed because I liked the taste. Finally, every time I come here I always come with my friends. I also always update on social media and recommend this restaurant to my other friends, even my friends from out of town. But yesterday will be the last time I eat here. Yesterday after I finished eating, one of their team came to the table asking if I had finished eating. If so, my time is up because Ive been there for 2 hours and the table is being used by another customer. At that time it was raining very heavily, so I waited for the rain to subside a bit. There were still around 6-8 empty tables there and no customers had come. Wang Li team please check CCTV 16/2/24 around 17.50-17.55. Then I asked, which customers would want to use this place? Because I didnt see any customers coming or wanting to use my table. Their team answered, THAT HAS BECOME THEIR RULES. OK, because I was kicked out, I left... I asked the cashier, the cashier said because there were only 3 sofa tables for 2 people, so who knows, someone might want to use it there. HAH? I asked, which person wants to use it? The cashier only apologized for his friends mistake. Honestly, I am very disappointed with the treatment of their team. It doesnt matter if that happens when the restaurant is very busy & there are new customers who dont get a table. I will voluntarily go. But in this situation, there are still a lot of empty tables... In fact, I have often eaten in busier places, where there are dozens of people standing on the waiting list, but I have never been kicked out like here, especially when this incident happened at the restaurant, there were still lots of tables. blank. I really dont think so. As much as I love your food, I would choose to eat somewhere else rather than come here again. Hopefully the restaurant team will read my review. Congratulations, you have lost one of your loyal customers. Starting today ME. NO. WILL. COME. TO. HERE. AGAIN. Thank You.

review_text: Cafe Tiga Ceret is the most famous cafe in Surakarta (Solo). It is a must for visitors or tourist to visit this cafe while visit this city. The cafe successfully elevates local traditional foods and beverages usualy serves in angkringan (street food vendor) at a level of cafe atmosphere but still maintain the affordability of the price. The cafe is located in a very strategic place on the center of Solo and in front of Mangkunegaran Castle with a lot of parking lot. The service is self service and fast. The ambient is spacious, consideribly clean and enjoyable but will always crowded on the weekend. The ornaments of the cafe use recycled material that make it unique. Local live music show regularly performs in this cafe. The foods are also unique and are specialties of Surakarta dishes, it used to be foods for commoner. For example you can find the Sego Kucing (small amount of rice, fried milkfish, and sambal, wrapped in banana leaf). They have their own name for this kind food, like Nasi Mercon (very spicy) etc. You can  grilled all the foods on a charcoal grill. Many kind of foods you can try in this cafe. They serve beverages that are also unique. Their special drink is Wedang Tiga Ceret (hot mix drink of ginger, lemon grass, lemon, sugar, and other herbs). Actually you can mix your own drink as you wish, for example, experimenting the mix of ginger with coffee and milk. This is becoming the philosophy of Tiga Ceret, Three Kettle. They serve also cold drink and other regular drink like coffee or tea. This cafe will always memorable for you with adventurous taste. Parking: If the place is crowded you can always find space not too far from the cafe. Kid-friendliness: Plenty of space Wheelchair accessibility: Wheelchair is accessible but not easy.

Patinnya cuma dapat 2 potong kecil kirain 1 ekor utuh ukuran kecil atau 1/2 ekor, ternyata cuma potongan kecil saja. Harga 5/5 Harga cukup terjangkau, walaupun udah ada pajak restoran.
review_translated_text: Place 5/5 Comfortable, spacious, quiet place. Traditional music is played which makes you relax. The food also came out quickly without waiting too long Food - tamarind vegetables 5/5 recommended, the taste is strong, spicy and tasty. - Grilled tilapia package 5/5 The package is quite complete at a price of 29 thousand and you get grilled tilapia, rice, fresh vegetables, tofu and tempeh, chili sauce and a drink. - pepes catfish 4/5 The spices dont have a kick when it comes to pepes, theyre not strong enough and theyre not spicy enough. You only get 2 small pieces of patin, I think its 1 whole small tail or 1/2 a tail, but it turns out its only small pieces. Price 5/5 Prices are quite affordable, even though there is restaurant tax.

Seperti warung makan pada umumnya. Masih bisa untuk menikmati makan di tempat. Cukup bersih dan luas. Tapi klau sedang ramai, harus bersabar menunggu karena meja dan kursi yang disediakan tidak begitu banyak. Saran saya reservasi terlebih dahulu apalagi jika mau makan ramai-ramai. Kami pesan beberapa menu dan yang bikin kami penasaran adalah sup asparagusnya. Untuk rasa secara keseluruhan lumayan. Bisa dijadikan pilihan jika bosan dengan menu di tempat makan yang biasa kalian kunjungi. Hanya saja sedikit kurang nendang bumbu-bumbunya. Tapi masih bisa dinikmati. review_translated_text: Always curious because every time you pass this road, the Mareme food stalls always look busy. Finally my family and I had the opportunity to eat at Mareme. The place is standard. Like food stalls in general. You can still enjoy eating on site. Quite clean and spacious. But if its busy, you have to be patient and wait because there arent that many tables and chairs provided. My advice is to make a reservation in advance, especially if you want to eat in a crowd. We ordered several menus and what made us curious was the asparagus soup. As for the overall taste, its not bad. It can be an option if you are bored with the menu at the restaurant you usually visit. Its just that the spices are a little lacking. But you can still enjoy it. Prices are also standard with prices for eating places in general. Portion is just right. There are some that are provided in large portions. Overall good.

I asked the waiter if I could order seafood fried noodles which were not listed on the menu, the service answered yes and finally I ordered it with warm lemon tea. After waiting about 15 minutes my food came. From the aroma it was very delicious, but after I looked around it turned out there were only 2 pinkie sized prawns. The rest is just meatballs and sausages. I dont know if the seafood fried noodles there are really like that or I heard it wrong. The taste is really good, the prices are still reasonable for some menus. Parking: Limited car parking

review_translated_text: Here I ordered the spicy one, I dont know what the name of the menu is and its really spicy but only on the outside. Is it because I ordered breasts? Wow, but even though the meat isnt spicy, its tender and not tough. Theres a little saltiness in it. The crackers werent thick (not too much flour). The rice is a bit soft, but thats okay. As for the crispy spinach/kailan, its not crispy enough. Then cut it into smaller pieces. The scamble eggs are delicious, they tend to be savory from the butter/margarine so theyre not too salty. The packaging is good and there is also tape so it doesnt open easily. Just... Why do you have to debit to pay? Why not just cash? Try explaining via social media the reasons why you use debit. If youve made it, maybe pin it on IG hahaha. So that people understand and when they come here they wont be surprised by a payment system like that. As for the place, I dont know what the atmosphere is like because I entrusted a friend here. Haha. So maybe thats it for now, my review~

review_translated_text: Assalamualaikum Good evening Dear Jatinangor House Soli branch (Banjarsari) Convey criticism and suggestions Straight to 1. What used to be cash is now debit. Maybe this is soup, but we as Solo residents who uphold Solo peoples etiquette, it seems like we dont respect/insult us because we dont have money, even though our intention is to buy and pay. 3. While we were there, the menu was rarely complete and there were definitely drawbacks, this has been a period of 1 year without any improvements or evaluations, right? If its not there, its useless, its better to just close it. We were disappointed that it actually made our favorites list! 1 year, no evaluation.

review_translated_text: Ive been a regular here since I was still dating Misua... I accidentally found this place and it turns out that the place is comfortable, cool, you can take a break for a while and the food is really delicious, especially the goat soup, beef soup and village chicken soup, plus the special chili sauce here, it makes eating delicious and you can eat it many times All the various soups are mutton, beef and free-range chicken, the satays are not that different in terms of taste, the spices are medok and thick... If every time you want to leave or go home from Uj Genteng, you always stop by here... Usually its free to eat as many fresh vegetables as you like, but today the vegetable seller was late so I couldnt eat any fresh vegetables... As for the price, its really friendly, its worth it for the taste it offers.. Oh yes, the bathroom is downstairs so you have to go downstairs, its not too far and the bathroom is very, very clean... Theres a prayer room too, you know

review_translated_text: I wanted satay/tengkleng in the morning, I went around to my regular place and it was sold out. I had to look on maps for a satay stall with a good rating. I found Pak Mos satay stall in the Nongko market area, hoping the food was delicious. I ordered tengkleng, cooked and tongseng. After ordering, it was ready. I brought it home and I was disappointed because the order I ordered wasnt the right one. I should have cooked tengkleng instead I was given tengkleng sauce. After all, it didnt taste good either. I had to eat while annoyed sorry, only giving stars

review_text: Review jujur ya hehe. Buat orang sabar recommended banget. Tapi kalo ga sabar ya jangan coba coba haha. Antri 20-25 menit, nunggu makanan 1 jam. Roti bakar juga enak, empuk, walaupun kecil tapi isianya banyak. Mendoan? Gatau rasanya karena ga nerima hehe. Satu setengah jam nunggu tapi ga dateng, pdhl antrian 50an dan pas nanya sudah sampai 70an, gatau sistem melayaninya gimana kok bisa sampe 70an pdhl yang 50an blm dilayani :) Mba nya bilang tunggu sebentar tapi 20 menit nunggu gadapat apapun, yaudah tinggal aja (cuma 5rb si tp uang wkwk) Not bad, harga nya murah dan lumayan enak, tapi kalo untuk dateng lagi? Ga dulu deh
review_translated_text: Honest review, hehe. For patient people, highly recommended. But if you cant wait, dont try it haha. Queue 20-25 minutes, wait for food 1 hour. In my opinion 50:50, not worth it but not too disappointing either. Order iced chocolate, mendoan and toast. The chocolate ice is delicious, its thick and very chocolatey. The toast is also delicious, soft, even though it is small, it has a lot of filling. Mendoan? I dont know what its like because I dont accept it hehe. Waited for an hour and a half but it didnt come, even though the queue was 50 and when I asked it was already up to 70, I dont know how the service system got it to 70 even though the 50 was not yet served :) The lady said wait a moment but 20 minutes of waiting and didnt get anything, so just stay (just 5 thousand but money hahaha) Not bad, the price is cheap and quite delicious, but what about coming back? Not yet

place_name: Food Court Solo Paragon Mall Lt. 2
review_text: Food Court di Solo Paragon Mall menawarkan pengalaman kuliner yang beragam dan memikat bagi para pengunjungnya. Terletak di lantai atas, suasana food court ini ramai dan nyaman, menjadi tempat yang ideal untuk menikmati makanan sambil bersantai. Dengan pilihan lebih dari 20 gerai makanan, pengunjung dapat menemukan berbagai hidangan mulai dari masakan lokal Jawa hingga makanan internasional yang lezat. Ada berbagai jenis masakan yang tersedia, mulai dari nasi goreng, sate, bakso, mie ayam, hingga pizza, burger, dan sushi. Setiap gerai memiliki keunikan dan keistimewaan tersendiri dalam penyajian dan rasa makanannya. Tidak hanya itu, food court ini juga menyediakan suasana yang bersih dan teratur dengan meja dan kursi yang nyaman bagi para pengunjungnya. Dengan harga yang terjangkau, food court Solo Paragon Mall menjadi tempat favorit bagi berbagai kalangan, baik wisatawan maupun warga lokal, untuk menikmati makanan yang lezat dan suasana yang menyenangkan. Selain itu, pilihan makanan yang variatif membuat food court ini cocok untuk acara makan bersama keluarga, teman, atau bahkan untuk rapat santai dengan rekan kerja. Dengan berbagai fasilitas yang tersedia, termasuk area bermain anak-anak, food court Solo Paragon Mall menjadi destinasi kuliner yang tidak boleh dilewatkan di Solo.
review_translated_text: The Food Court at Solo Paragon Mall offers a diverse and attractive culinary experience for its visitors. Located on the top floor, the atmosphere of this food court is lively and comfortable, making it an ideal place to enjoy food while relaxing. With a choice of more than 20 food outlets, visitors can find a variety of dishes ranging from local Javanese dishes to international delicacies. There are various types of dishes available, from fried rice, satay, meatballs, chicken noodles, to pizza, burgers and sushi. Each outlet has its own uniqueness and specialty in the presentation and taste of its food. Not only that, this food court also provides a clean and orderly atmosphere with comfortable tables and chairs for its visitors. With affordable prices, the Solo Paragon Mall food court is a favorite place for various groups, both tourists and local residents, to enjoy delicious food and a pleasant atmosphere. Apart from that, the varied food choices make this food court suitable for meals with family, friends, or even for casual meetings with colleagues. With various facilities available, including a childrens play area, the Solo Paragon Mall food court is a culinary destination that should not be missed in Solo.

There are croissants, tuna puffs, there are also ones filled with cream and blueberry jam (forgot the name   ) Each table also has an electric plug so its definitely very convenient for doing work. There is also a separate room if you want to have a meeting here.

review_text: dateng ga ekspek apa-apa, pesen beef hambugo dapet free es teh kalau dine in, turns out di dalem hambugo nya itu ada mozza sama mashed potatoes      milih mushroom sauce dan... di dalamnya ada burnt cheese slice overall nice gewd, hambugo kalau bisa dapet smokey flavornya bakal jadi the best hambugo sih        mushroom sauce bisa lebih creamy lagi yuk tempat smol muat 8-10 orang indoor, hampir takeaway karena full haha untung ada yang selesai serving food cepet nice, dateng mandiri liat menu sendiri karena staffnya sibuk preparing food, tapi mas nya ramah kok Parking: kalau bawa mobil, saingan parkir sama nasi liwet dan tenant lain :)
